It was sad and beautiful to witness these salmon return from the sea to pass away. Salmon are able to return to their home tributaries thanks to their keen sense of smell and their ability to detect magnetic fields. The salmon lifecycle is one of the few in nature in which nutrients from the sea are brought back to land to feed the plants and animals that reside near the rivers.
